Day 5 complete.
More reading than typing today :(

Day 14 complete
Today was about socket.io.
starting to realize this 30days of node website didnt get much love during its
creation. spelling and grammtical error everywhere.

Haven't been focusing on the html and css of the tutorial. that not what im trying to
learn right now. the server side stuff, and little jquery is really fun
that was done today was my main focus
Skipping this day. MongoDB gave me many problems
learn concept of taking input from front end

Day 13 complete
Today was the first project lesson. I focused more on the server.js file.

Day 12 complete
After some research I learned the reason i was having a problem
yesterday was because the mongodb module was updated.
Needed to add "db.db('demo_db')" to all the files.
Going to work on learning some MongoDB in another tutorial before moving on

Day 17 complete
I couldn't connect anything to an mysql database and couldn't figure out why.
given that im already comfortable with sql I figured i dont need to run these
scripts. Found them self-explanatory

Day 27 complete
Found this lesson really boring and kind of useless :/

Day 28 complete
There was an error that would crash the server.
It looked like the server wasn't getting data when the socket.emit() executes

Day 23 complete
no coding in this one. The website talked about the built-in debugger in node.
I don't see myself using this cause I use vscode which has a very nice debugger interface
Changed alt-click to shift-click cause alt-click has a different functionality on different OS's
fixed error where all bombs wouldn't show when the game is lost
updated shapes to be able to control line width
Added flagging and a little tutorial on how to play the game
Made it so the user can unflag a cell. I now clear the board every update so things dont draw over themselves. Looks cleaner after a couple of clicks
Added small winner/loser div. Probably going to change and improve later
Moved css into its own file
got rid of ticker idea. The game doesnt need to be updated in increments of time, ill just update it when the user clicks the screen
Fixed bug that made squares too big
did some math to figure out where the user is clicking on the canvas instead of on the whole webpage
not much has changed. Mostly how im drawing the game

Drawing
since I am not able to use p5 for drawing anymore, i made a function to
help draw basic shapes
I've never made an online website, only on my local machine. Fixed urls for scripts
idk what to make these urls. I keep getting 404 errors
Changed position and look of title div
game now restarts automatically so the user doesnt have to reload page
put link to game in read me

O(n) to O(1)

got rid of clicked in cell class which required me to loop through all
the cells in the grid. Now i just do the math in mouseClick to find the
index of the clicked on cell. This has a faster run time
